'''Abdullah ibn Khatal''' (died 629 C.E.) was a [[Muslim]] [[tax collector]] who committed [[treason]] against the [[Constitution of Medina|State of Medina]] by defecting to [[Mecca]] and becoming an [[Apostate]]. He was killed shortly after the [[Conquest of Mecca]] on the orders of [[Muhammad]] being one of the 12 inhabitants of Mecca not granted immunity. It is said that he was hanging to the curtains of the [[Kaaba]] in [[Mecca]], where he attempted to take refuge but was executed before being able to enter the Ka'aba .<ref name="Anas2013">{{cite book|author=Anas|title=Al-Muwatta Of Iman Malik Ibn Ana|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZUTYAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA171|date=28 October 2013|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-136-15098-2|pages=171–}}</ref><ref>{{hadith-usc|usc=yes|Bukhari|5|59|582}}</ref>
