{{Infobox person |name=John Bloom |image= |image_size= |caption= |occupation=[[Actor]] |birth_date={{birth date|1944|2|19}} |birth_place=[[Los Angeles]], California, U.S. |death_date={{death date and age|1999|1|15|1944|2|19}} |death_place=Los Angeles, California, U.S. }}
'''John Bloom''' (February 19, 1944 – January 15, 1999) was an American actor.<ref name=NYT>{{cite web|work=[[The New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/movies/person/628477/John-Bloom|title=John Bloom}}</ref>
==Career== Standing at 7' 4" (224&nbsp;cm) tall, he is most famous for his roles as [[Frankenstein's Monster]] in the low-budget horror movie ''[[Dracula vs. Frankenstein]]'', and the unfortunate recipient in ''[[The Incredible 2-Headed Transplant]]''.
He also had a role in ''The Dark'' then parts in ''[[Bachelor Party (1984 film)|Bachelor Party]]'', ''[[The Hills Have Eyes Part II]]'', ''[[Harry and the Hendersons]]'', and ''[[Star Trek VI: The Undiscovered Country]]'' followed. He played the blacksmith "Tiny" on the TV series "Paradise" and "Guns of Paradise."
Bloom died from [[heart failure]] brought on by his immense height{{cn|date=October 2018}} on January 15, 1999 in his home city of [[Los Angeles]].
